            <abstract xml:lang="en">
              <p>We present a new approach to perform zeroshot cross-modal transfer between speech and text for translation tasks. Multilingual speech and text are encoded in a joint fixed-size representation space. Then, we compare different approaches to decode these multimodal and multilingual fixed-size representations, enabling zero-shot translation between languages and modalities. All our models are trained without the need of cross-modal labeled translation data. Despite a fixed-size representation, we achieve very competitive results on several text and speech translation tasks. In particular, we outperform the state of the art for zero-shot speech translation on Must-C. We also introduce the first results for zero-shot direct speechto-speech and text-to-speech translation.</p>
            </abstract>
